# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010000> (raw material)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010000>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "Whether a material is raw material depends on its participation in a particular production or recycling workflow."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "raw material"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A material entity that is intended to be consumed, transformed, or incorporated as input in a manufacturing, recycling, or material processing process."@en,
    skos:example
      "PA66 pellets supplied to an injection molding process as input material."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:BFO_0000040


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010001> (additive)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010001>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "This class represents the additive material itself; the context-dependent function is represented by additive role."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "additive"@en,
    skos:definition
      "An engineered material intentionally incorporated in a base material in a comparatively small amount to modify processing behavior, performance properties, appearance, or cost."@en,
    skos:example
      "A UV stabilizer added to an exterior polymer trim material."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000002


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010002> (matrix)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010002>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "The corresponding realizable entity is PMD Core matrix role; this class is used for material entities considered as the continuous phase of a composite."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "matrix"@en,
    skos:definition
      "An engineered material that forms the continuous phase of a composite material and binds or embeds reinforcement, filler, or dispersed material constituents."@en,
    skos:example
      "The PA66 phase in a PA66-GF25 composite."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000002


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010003> (water absorption)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010003>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "Values are normally reported for specified test conditions, such as ISO 62 or a specified conditioning atmosphere."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "water absorption"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A disposition of a material to take up water from a liquid water or humid environment under specified exposure conditions."@en,
    skos:example
      "The percentage mass increase of a polyamide specimen after immersion in water."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:BFO_0000016


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010004> (materials information)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010004>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label
      "materials information"@en,
    skos:definition
      "An information content entity that specifies material-related characteristics of a product, component, material batch, or material grade."@en,
    skos:example
      "A data record listing material designation, density, fiber content, and recycled content for an automotive component."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:IAO_0000030


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010005> (material composition)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010005>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label
      "material composition"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A composition that describes the material constituents and constituent amounts of a product, component, material batch, or material grade."@en,
    skos:example
      "A composition stating that PA66-GF25 contains a PA66 matrix and nominally 25 percent glass fiber by mass."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0025001


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010006> (recycled material)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010006>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "This class covers material entities whose origin is a recycling process; the amount or share of recycled content should be represented separately."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "recycled material"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A material entity that has been recovered from waste, discarded products, by-products, or production residues through a recycling process for subsequent use."@en,
    skos:example
      "Regranulated polypropylene produced from end-of-life vehicle parts."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:BFO_0000040


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010007> (recycled)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010007>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "Use for the origin state of a material; use recycled material share for quantities or proportions."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "recycled"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A quality of a material entity indicating that the material has an origin in a recycling process rather than only in primary material production."@en,
    skos:example
      "A recycled quality borne by a polymer regrind used in a new injection molding batch."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:BFO_0000019


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010100> (environmental condition)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010100>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "environmental condition"@en,
    skos:definition "A quality of an environment that is relevant to material behavior, processing, testing, storage, use, or degradation."@en,
    skos:example "A conditioning atmosphere with specified temperature and relative humidity."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:BFO_0000019


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010101> (filler)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010101>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment "The role borne by such a material in a composite is PMD Core filler role."@en,
    rdfs:label "filler"@en,
    skos:definition "An engineered material incorporated in another material to occupy volume, modify properties, reduce cost, or contribute reinforcement in a composite or compound."@en,
    skos:example "Glass fibers or mineral particles added to a polymer compound."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000002


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010102> (reinforcement)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010102>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment "The Excel hint to PMD Core filler role was modeled as a material class here because the glossary term names the reinforcing material, not only the role."@en,
    rdfs:label "reinforcement"@en,
    skos:definition "A filler material that is incorporated into a matrix material to improve load-bearing, stiffness, strength, impact, or dimensional performance."@en,
    skos:example "Chopped glass fiber used as reinforcement in PA66-GF25."@en

  SubClassOf:
    <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010101>


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010103> (further content)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010103>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "further content"@en,
    skos:definition "A composition data item that records additional material constituents or content fractions not captured by the primary material composition fields."@en,
    skos:example "A data item recording minor additive content in a polymer compound."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:IAO_0000027


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010104> (water content)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010104>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment "The Excel source references ISO 15512 for plastics water content measurement."@en,
    rdfs:label "water content"@en,
    skos:definition "A mass proportion that quantifies the amount of water contained in a material under specified measurement or conditioning conditions."@en,
    skos:example "Water content of a polyamide granulate measured before injection molding."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020102


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010105> (ash content)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010105>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment "The Excel source references ISO 3451 for ash content, often used to estimate inorganic filler content."@en,
    rdfs:label "ash content"@en,
    skos:definition "A mass proportion that quantifies the inorganic residue remaining after controlled combustion or calcination of a material sample."@en,
    skos:example "Ash content used to estimate glass fiber or mineral filler content in a polymer compound."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020102


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010106> (material class)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010106>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "material class"@en,
    skos:definition "An information content entity that assigns a material, component, or product to a material category in a stated classification scheme."@en,
    skos:example "A VDA 231-106 material class assignment for polymer materials."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:IAO_0000030


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010107> (material abbreviation)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010107>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "material abbreviation"@en,
    skos:definition "An identifier that records a short material designation or abbreviation used for a material or material family."@en,
    skos:example "PA66-GF25 as an abbreviated designation for a glass-fiber-reinforced polyamide 66 compound."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:IAO_0020000


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010108> (manufacturing simulation)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010108>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "manufacturing simulation"@en,
    skos:definition "A simulation process that represents a manufacturing process and its material, process, geometry, or performance consequences."@en,
    skos:example "A simulation of an injection molding process used to predict filling and cooling behavior."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000933


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010109> (injection molding simulation)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010109>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "injection molding simulation"@en,
    skos:definition "A manufacturing simulation that represents an injection molding process, including relevant material, mold, filling, packing, cooling, or warpage behavior."@en,
    skos:example "A mold-filling simulation for a PA66-GF25 housing."@en

  SubClassOf:
    <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010108>


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010110> (quasistatic simulation)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010110>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "quasistatic simulation"@en,
    skos:definition "A simulation process that represents material or component response under loading conditions where inertial effects are negligible."@en,
    skos:example "A quasistatic finite element simulation of a bracket under service load."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000933


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010111> (thermal simulation)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010111>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "thermal simulation"@en,
    skos:definition "A simulation process that represents heat transfer, temperature distribution, or thermally induced material behavior."@en,
    skos:example "A cooling simulation for an injection molded component."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000933


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010112> (quasistatic stress normal)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010112>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "quasistatic stress normal"@en,
    skos:definition "A strength-related material or simulation output quality that represents stress normal to a reference direction under quasistatic loading."@en,
    skos:example "Normal stress predicted by a quasistatic simulation perpendicular to fiber orientation."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000952


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010113> (quasistatic stress parallel)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010113>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "quasistatic stress parallel"@en,
    skos:definition "A strength-related material or simulation output quality that represents stress parallel to a reference direction under quasistatic loading."@en,
    skos:example "Stress predicted parallel to fiber orientation in a quasistatic simulation."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000952


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010114> (quasistatic strain normal)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010114>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "quasistatic strain normal"@en,
    skos:definition "A mechanical property or simulation output quality that represents strain normal to a reference direction under quasistatic loading."@en,
    skos:example "Normal strain predicted perpendicular to fiber orientation in a quasistatic simulation."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000848


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010115> (quasistatic strain parallel)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010115>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "quasistatic strain parallel"@en,
    skos:definition "A mechanical property or simulation output quality that represents strain parallel to a reference direction under quasistatic loading."@en,
    skos:example "Strain predicted parallel to fiber orientation in a quasistatic simulation."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000848


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010116> (elongation expansion normal)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010116>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "elongation expansion normal"@en,
    skos:definition "A length-related quality or simulation output that represents elongation or expansion normal to a reference direction."@en,
    skos:example "Thermal expansion normal to fiber orientation in a molded composite."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0040001


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010117> (elongation expansion parallel)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010117>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "elongation expansion parallel"@en,
    skos:definition "A length-related quality or simulation output that represents elongation or expansion parallel to a reference direction."@en,
    skos:example "Thermal expansion parallel to fiber orientation in a molded composite."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0040001


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010118> (length of fibers)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010118>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "length of fibers"@en,
    skos:definition "A length quality that quantifies the characteristic or measured length of fibers in a fiber-containing material."@en,
    skos:example "Mean glass fiber length after injection molding of PA66-GF25."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0040001


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010119> (reutilization material share)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010119>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "reutilization material share"@en,
    skos:definition "A mass proportion that quantifies the share of material from rework, regrind, or scrap that is reused within the process or production system that generated it."@en,
    skos:example "The percentage of in-process regrind returned to an injection molding feedstock."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020102


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010120> (origin)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010120>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "origin"@en,
    skos:definition "An information content entity that records the source category, provenance, or supply-chain origin of a material."@en,
    skos:example "An origin statement that a polymer fraction is post-consumer automotive recycled material."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:IAO_0000030


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010121> (pre-consumer material share)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010121>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "pre-consumer material share"@en,
    skos:definition "A mass proportion that quantifies material content originating from pre-consumer production residues, by-products, rework, or scrap."@en,
    skos:example "The share of molding scrap reused before the product reached a consumer."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020102


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010122> (post-consumer material share)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010122>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "post-consumer material share"@en,
    skos:definition "A mass proportion that quantifies material content originating from products or materials recovered after consumer or user service."@en,
    skos:example "The share of polypropylene recovered from end-of-life vehicle parts."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020102


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010123> (material source share)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010123>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "material source share"@en,
    skos:definition "A mass proportion that quantifies the share of material from a stated source category, such as primary, secondary, pre-consumer, post-consumer, automotive, or non-automotive sources."@en,
    skos:example "A material source share for secondary automotive recycled content."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020102


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010124> (other recycling information)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010124>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "other recycling information"@en,
    skos:definition "A document or information content entity that provides additional evidence, provenance, compliance, or quality information about material origin or recycling."@en,
    skos:example "A supplier declaration documenting recycled material origin and quality."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:IAO_0000310


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010125> (automotive material share)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010125>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "automotive material share"@en,
    skos:definition "A mass proportion that quantifies the share of material content originating from automotive sources."@en,
    skos:example "The fraction of recycled polymer sourced from end-of-life vehicle components."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020102


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010126> (non-automotive material share)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010126>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "non-automotive material share"@en,
    skos:definition "A mass proportion that quantifies the share of material content originating from non-automotive sources."@en,
    skos:example "The fraction of recycled polymer sourced from consumer packaging rather than vehicle components."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020102


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010127> (secondary material)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010127>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "secondary material"@en,
    skos:definition "A material entity obtained from waste, by-products, production residues, or recovered products and intended to substitute for primary material in a production process."@en,
    skos:example "A recycled polymer regranulate used as feedstock for a new automotive component."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:BFO_0000040


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010128> (primary material)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010128>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "primary material"@en,
    skos:definition "A material entity produced from virgin raw resources and used for the first time in a production process."@en,
    skos:example "Virgin PA66 resin produced from primary chemical feedstocks."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:BFO_0000040


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010129> (physical dimension)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0010129>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:label "physical dimension"@en,
    skos:definition "A quality that characterizes a physical extent or dimensional feature of a material entity, product, component, or geometric feature."@en,
    skos:example "Length, width, thickness, or diameter used to characterize an automotive component."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:BFO_0000019

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000002> (raw material role)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000002>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment 
      "This role is realized when the material enters the supply chain or the hopper of a processing machine."@en,
    rdfs:label 
      "raw material role"@en,
    skos:definition 
      "A role borne by a material entity when it functions as an input to a manufacturing process prior to transformation or processing."@en,
    skos:example 
      "Plastic granules sitting in a silo waiting to be fed into an extruder bear this role."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:BFO_0000023

    
# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000003> (additive role)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000003>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "Additives are distinct from fillers (which bulk up volume) and the matrix. They perform specific chemical or physical modifications."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "additive role"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A role borne by a substance intentionally added in relatively small amounts to modify the processing characteristics, performance properties, or cost of a base material."@en,
    skos:example
      "UV stabilizers added to dashboard polymers to prevent sun damage; Plasticizers added to PVC."@en

  SubClassOf:
    obo:BFO_0000023


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000004> (organic colorant)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000004>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "Organic colorants (dyes) offer high color strength and brightness but may have lower thermal stability than pigments."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "organic colorant"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A complex organic chemical compound used to impart color, typically soluble in the medium."@en,
    skos:example
      "Azo dyes used in interior textile coloring."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000868

  DisjointWith:
    <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000005>


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000005> (inorganic colorant)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000005>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "Inorganic colorants (pigments) are generally insoluble and provide opacity and high heat stability."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "inorganic colorant"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A mineral-based chemical compound, usually an oxide or sulfide, used to impart color."@en,
    skos:example
      "Titanium dioxide (white) used in car paints."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000002


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000006> (colorant role)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000006>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "This role can be borne by organic dyes or inorganic pigments."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "colorant role"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A role borne by an additive substance when its primary function is to impart color to a material."@en,
    skos:example
      "Carbon black acting as a pigment to turn a tire black."@en

  SubClassOf:
    <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000003>


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000008> (color)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000008>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "Can be defined descriptively (Red) or metrologically (L*a*b* coordinates)."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "color"@en,
    skos:definition
      "The quality of an object or substance with respect to light reflected by the object, usually determined visually by measurement of hue, saturation, and brightness."@en,
    skos:example
      "The 'Piano Black' finish on a B-pillar trim."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020131


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000009> (polyamide)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000009>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "Polyamides are semi-crystalline polymers known for good thermal and chemical resistance."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "polyamide"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A polymer containing repeating amide (-CONH-) linkages in the polymer backbone."@en,
    skos:example
      "Nylon 6, Nylon 12, Nylon 66."@en,
    pmd:PMD_0050117
      "PA"

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0050004


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000010> (PA66)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000010>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "PA66 has a higher melting point (~260°C) than PA6 but absorbs moisture which affects dimensional stability."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "PA66"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A semicrystalline thermoplastic polyamide synthesized from hexamethylenediamine and adipic acid."@en,
    skos:example
      "Material used for cylinder head covers and radiator end tanks."@en,
    pmd:PMD_0050117
      "PA66"

  SubClassOf:
    <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000009>


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000011> (PA66-GF25)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000011>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "The addition of 25% glass fiber significantly increases stiffness and tensile strength compared to neat PA66."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "PA66-GF25"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A composite material consisting of a Polyamide 66 matrix reinforced with 25% glass fiber by mass."@en,
    skos:example
      "Structural components in the engine bay requiring high stiffness at elevated temperatures."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000577


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000012> (fiber)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000012>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "In PMD logic, this is a disconnected aggregate because the individual filaments in a bundle are distinct objects."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "fiber"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A class of materials that are continuous filaments or are in discrete elongated pieces, similar to lengths of thread."@en,
    skos:example
      "Carbon fiber tow, Aramid fibers."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000891


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000013> (glass fiber)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000013>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "Used extensively as a reinforcement agent in polymer matrix composites."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "glass fiber"@en,
    skos:definition
      "A material consisting of numerous extremely fine fibers of glass."@en,
    skos:example
      "E-Glass used to reinforce PA66 for automotive pedals."@en,
    pmd:PMD_0050117
      "GF"

  SubClassOf:
    <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000012>


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000014> (fiber material content mass fraction)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000014>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "Commonly denoted as wt%. PA66-GF25 implies a value of 0.25 or 25%."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "fiber material content mass fraction"@en,
    skos:definition
      "The ratio of the mass of the fiber reinforcement to the total mass of the composite material."@en,
    skos:example
      "25% mass fraction in PA66-GF25."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020102


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000015> (fiber material content volume fraction)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000015>

  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment
      "Volume fraction is more critical for micromechanical modeling (e.g., Rule of Mixtures) than mass fraction."@en,
    rdfs:label
      "fiber material content volume fraction"@en,
    skos:definition
      "The ratio of the volume of the fiber reinforcement to the total volume of the composite material."@en,
    skos:example
      "Approximately 14-15% volume fraction corresponds to 25% mass fraction for Glass/PA66."@en

  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020104

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000023> (viscosity)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000023>
  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment "Critical for injection molding simulations to predict mold filling."@en,
    rdfs:label "viscosity"@en,
    skos:definition "A measure of a fluid's resistance to flow."@en,
    skos:example "The melt viscosity of polypropylene at 230°C."@en
  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020131

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000025> (shear viscosity)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000025>
  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment "Polymers are non-Newtonian; their shear viscosity decreases as shear rate increases (shear thinning)."@en,
    rdfs:label "shear viscosity"@en,
    skos:definition "The viscosity of a fluid when subjected to shear stress; defined as the ratio of shear stress to shear rate."@en,
    skos:example "Viscosity curve data required for Moldflow simulation."@en
  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020131


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000026> (glass transition temperature)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000026>
  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment "Below Tg, the amorphous phase is frozen; above Tg, polymer chains have mobility."@en,
    rdfs:label "glass transition temperature"@en,
    skos:definition "The temperature range where a polymer material transitions from a hard, glassy material to a soft, rubbery material."@en,
    skos:example "Tg of approx. 50°C for dry PA66."@en,
    pmd:PMD_0050117 "Tg"
  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000882


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000027> (coefficient of linear thermal expansion)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000027>
  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment "Crucial for calculating gap and flush in automotive assembly where different materials (steel vs plastic) meet."@en,
    rdfs:label "coefficient of linear thermal expansion"@en,
    skos:definition "The fractional change in length per degree of temperature change."@en,
    skos:example "CLTE is distinct in flow-direction vs cross-flow direction for fiber reinforced parts."@en,
    pmd:PMD_0050117 "CLTE"
  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000981


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000028> (specific heat capacity)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000028>
  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment "Used to calculate cooling times in injection molding."@en,
    rdfs:label "specific heat capacity"@en,
    skos:definition "The amount of heat energy required to raise the temperature of a substance per unit of mass."@en,
    skos:example "1700 J/(kg·K) for Polypropylene."@en,
    pmd:PMD_0050117 "Cp"
  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0000981


# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000032> (humidity)

Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/automatce/AUTOMATCE_0000032>
  Annotations:
    rdfs:comment "Crucial for PA66 as it absorbs moisture, changing its mechanical properties (conditioning)."@en,
    rdfs:label "humidity"@en,
    skos:definition "The concentration of water vapor present in the air or environment surrounding a material."@en,
    skos:example "50% Relative Humidity (standard conditioning atmosphere)."@en
  SubClassOf:
    pmd:PMD_0020131


